Practical priority order

1. ONNX Runtime first

Best abstraction for Beast2 now.

ONNX Runtime is explicitly built around "Execution Providers," meaning one model runtime can target CUDA, TensorRT, DirectML, CoreML, OpenVINO, etc.  ￼

For Beast2:

beast graph
  -> onnx runtime
      -> cuda ep
      -> tensorrt ep
      -> directml ep
      -> coreml ep
      -> openvino ep
      -> cpu fallback

2. NVIDIA CUDA/TensorRT for power users

This is the "it actually runs fast" path.

Windows/Linux + NVIDIA RTX
ONNX Runtime CUDA EP first
TensorRT EP later for optimized deployment

3. DirectML for Windows compatibility

Good fallback when user has random GPU.

Windows + AMD/Intel/NVIDIA
ONNX Runtime DirectML EP

